text: Terebra jacksoniana is a species of sea snail, a marine gastropod mollusk in the family Terebridae, the auger snails. ==Description== ==Distribution== This species is native to regions of Australia including Ballina, New South Wales and south-eastern South Australia. Sea shells of New South Wales ==References== Category:Terebridae Category:Gastropods described in 1976
title: Terebra jacksoniana
